The adventures of a gang of British workmen abroad. Britain's favourite
brickies reunite for their final adventure... but will Thailand ever
recover? 

Following a narrow escape from a British Embassy in Africa besieged by
rioters, the lads relocate to the Australian Embassy in Laos for their
next job. Whilst at work, after all their adventures, one by one the
boys start realising there's more to lifew than being part of their
gang - a feeling brought into sharp focus after a letter arrives from
Bomber telling them he's swapping his trowel for a settled family life.
On succesfully completing the job, and sensing this could be the last 
time they're all together, the boys make big plans for some rest and
relaxation in Thailand, but it's not long before events and a familiar 
enemy conspire against them, and rest and relaxation are a distant memory.
